00:21:13.849 --> 00:21:16.849
The servants attend to them,

00:21:16.849 --> 00:21:19.849
getting them ready for the day's journey.

00:21:19.849 --> 00:21:23.849
But then, come cries of alarm.

00:21:23.849 --> 00:21:26.849
Laban has come, and he's not alone.

00:21:26.849 --> 00:21:29.849
He arrives with strong men.

00:21:29.849 --> 00:21:31.849
They gallop in on camels.

00:21:31.849 --> 00:21:33.849
They dismount.

00:21:33.849 --> 00:21:37.849
This is not a friendly visit.

00:21:37.849 --> 00:21:42.849
Laban's men are ready to obey orders from Laban.

00:21:42.849 --> 00:21:45.849
Jacob's servants quickly gather to the scene.

00:21:45.849 --> 00:21:51.849
All eyes are fixed on Laban and Jacob who argue.

00:21:51.849 --> 00:21:53.849
The previous night,

00:21:53.849 --> 00:21:56.849
Jehovah had warned Laban in a dream

00:21:56.849 --> 00:22:00.849
to be careful about what he'd say to Jacob.

00:22:00.849 --> 00:22:06.849
Still, Laban is angry and aggressive.

00:22:06.849 --> 00:22:09.849
Laban makes two charges.

00:22:09.849 --> 00:22:11.849
First, he says,

00:22:11.849 --> 00:22:14.849
Why have you resorted to outwitting me

00:22:14.849 --> 00:22:19.849
and carrying my daughters off like captives taken by the sword?

00:22:19.849 --> 00:22:26.849
Why did you run away secretly and outwit me and not tell me?

00:22:26.849 --> 00:22:29.849
The answer to that charge is obvious.

00:22:29.849 --> 00:22:31.849
Jacob replies,

00:22:31.849 --> 00:22:34.849
It was because I was afraid,

00:22:34.849 --> 00:22:36.849
I said to myself,

00:22:36.849 --> 00:22:40.849
You might take your daughters away from me by force.

00:22:40.849 --> 00:22:46.849
Laban also charges that Jacob has stolen his household gods.

00:22:46.849 --> 00:22:50.849
Rachel has indeed stolen the gods,

00:22:50.849 --> 00:22:53.849
but Jacob knows nothing about this.

00:22:53.849 --> 00:22:55.849
A search is made,

00:22:55.849 --> 00:22:58.849
but the idols are not found.

00:22:58.849 --> 00:23:01.849
Jacob then makes his defense.

00:23:01.849 --> 00:23:06.849
Let's take up our reading at Genesis chapter 31 and verse 36.

00:23:06.849 --> 00:23:10.450
At that,

00:23:10.450 --> 00:23:14.450
Jacob became angry and began to criticize Laban.

00:23:14.450 --> 00:23:17.450
Jacob then said to Laban,

00:23:17.450 --> 00:23:19.450
What is my offense?

00:23:19.450 --> 00:23:22.450
And for what sin are you hotly pursuing me?

00:23:22.450 --> 00:23:25.450
Now that you have searched through all my goods,

00:23:25.450 --> 00:23:28.450
what have you found that belongs to your house?

00:23:28.450 --> 00:23:31.450
Put it here in front of my brothers and your brothers

00:23:31.450 --> 00:23:35.450
and let them decide between the two of us.

00:23:35.450 --> 00:23:38.450
During these twenty years that I have been with you,

00:23:38.450 --> 00:23:42.450
your sheep and your goats never miscarried,

00:23:42.450 --> 00:23:45.450
and I never ate the rams of your flock.

00:23:45.450 --> 00:23:49.450
I did not bring you any animal torn by wild beasts.

00:23:49.450 --> 00:23:52.450
I would stand the loss of it myself.

00:23:52.450 --> 00:23:55.450
Whether the animal was stolen by day,

00:23:55.450 --> 00:23:57.450
or was stolen by night,

00:23:57.450 --> 00:24:00.450
you would demand compensation from me.

00:24:00.450 --> 00:24:03.450
By day, the heat consumed me,

00:24:03.450 --> 00:24:05.450
and the cold by night,

00:24:05.450 --> 00:24:08.450
and sleep would flee from my eyes.

00:24:08.450 --> 00:24:12.450
This makes twenty years for me in your house.

00:24:12.450 --> 00:24:16.450
I have served you fourteen years for your two daughters,

00:24:16.450 --> 00:24:18.450
and six years for your flock,

00:24:18.450 --> 00:24:22.450
and you kept changing my wages ten times.

00:24:22.450 --> 00:24:25.450
If the God of my Father,

00:24:25.450 --> 00:24:27.450
the God of Abraham,

00:24:27.450 --> 00:24:31.450
whom Isaac fears had not been on my side,

00:24:31.450 --> 00:24:35.450
you would now have sent me away empty handed.

00:24:35.450 --> 00:24:37.450
God has seen my affliction,

00:24:37.450 --> 00:24:39.450
and the toil of my hands,

00:24:39.450 --> 00:24:42.450
and that is why he reproved you last night.

00:24:42.450 --> 00:24:45.450
Then, Laban answered Jacob.

00:24:45.450 --> 00:24:47.450
The daughters are my daughters,

00:24:47.450 --> 00:24:49.450
and the children, my children,

00:24:49.450 --> 00:24:51.450
and the flock, my flock,

00:24:51.450 --> 00:24:55.450
and everything you are looking at is mine.

00:24:55.450 --> 00:24:58.450
And my daughters,

00:24:58.450 --> 00:25:00.450
what can I do today against these

00:25:00.450 --> 00:25:04.450
or against their children whom they have born?

00:25:04.450 --> 00:25:07.450
Now come, let us make a covenant,

00:25:07.450 --> 00:25:08.450
you and I,

00:25:08.450 --> 00:25:12.450
and it will serve as a witness between us.

00:25:12.450 --> 00:25:14.450
So Jacob took a stone

00:25:14.450 --> 00:25:16.450
and set it up as a pillar.

00:25:16.450 --> 00:25:19.450
Then Jacob said to his brothers,

00:25:19.450 --> 00:25:21.450
pick up stones,

00:25:21.450 --> 00:25:24.450
and they took stones and made a pile,

00:25:24.450 --> 00:25:26.450
after that,

00:25:26.450 --> 00:25:29.450
they ate there on the pile of stones.

00:25:29.450 --> 00:25:33.450
And Laban began calling at Jigarse Hadootha,

00:25:33.450 --> 00:25:36.450
but Jacob called a galliad.

00:25:36.450 --> 00:25:38.450
Laban then said,

00:25:38.450 --> 00:25:40.450
This pile of stones is a witness

00:25:40.450 --> 00:25:43.450
between me and you today.

00:25:43.450 --> 00:25:46.450
That is why he named it galliad,

00:25:46.450 --> 00:25:48.450
and the watchtower,

00:25:48.450 --> 00:25:49.450
for he said,

00:25:49.450 --> 00:25:53.450
Let Jehovah keep watch between you and me

00:25:53.450 --> 00:25:56.450
when we are out of each other's sight.

00:25:56.450 --> 00:25:58.450
If you mistreat my daughters,

00:25:58.450 --> 00:26:00.450
and if you start taking wives

00:26:00.450 --> 00:26:02.450
in addition to my daughters,

00:26:02.450 --> 00:26:04.450
though there is no man with us,

00:26:04.450 --> 00:26:07.450
remember that God will be a witness

00:26:07.450 --> 00:26:09.450
between you and me.

00:26:09.450 --> 00:26:12.450
Laban went on to say to Jacob,

00:26:12.450 --> 00:26:15.450
Here is this pile of stones,

00:26:15.450 --> 00:26:17.450
and here is the pillar

00:26:17.450 --> 00:26:20.450
that I have erected between you and me.

00:26:20.450 --> 00:26:23.450
This pile of stones is a witness,

00:26:23.450 --> 00:26:26.450
and the pillar is something that bears witness,

00:26:26.450 --> 00:26:29.450
that I will not pass beyond this pile of stones

00:26:29.450 --> 00:26:31.450
to bring harm to you,

00:26:31.450 --> 00:26:34.450
and you will not pass beyond this pile of stones

00:26:34.450 --> 00:26:37.450
and this pillar to bring harm to me.

00:26:37.450 --> 00:26:40.450
Let the God of Abraham and the God of Nahor,

00:26:40.450 --> 00:26:42.450
the God of their Father,

00:26:42.450 --> 00:26:45.450
judge between us.

00:26:45.450 --> 00:26:50.450
And Jacob swore by the one whom his father Isaac fears.

00:26:50.450 --> 00:26:52.450
After that,

00:26:52.450 --> 00:26:55.450
Jacob offered a sacrifice in the mountain

00:26:55.450 --> 00:26:58.450
and invited his brothers to eat bread,

00:26:58.450 --> 00:27:02.450
so they ate and spent the night in the mountain.

00:27:02.450 --> 00:27:05.450
However, Laban got up early in the morning

00:27:05.450 --> 00:27:08.450
and kissed his grandchildren and his daughters

00:27:08.450 --> 00:27:10.450
and blessed them.

00:27:10.450 --> 00:27:17.170
Then Laban departed and returned home.

00:27:17.170 --> 00:27:22.170
Jacob had served Laban faithfully for 20 years,

00:27:22.170 --> 00:27:26.170
even though Laban had defrauded and exploited him.

00:27:26.170 --> 00:27:28.170
Laban doesn't acknowledge that,

00:27:28.170 --> 00:27:31.170
but rather dishonestly claims

00:27:31.170 --> 00:27:36.170
that he is the rightful owner of all that Jacob has with him.

00:27:36.170 --> 00:27:41.170
Laban then suggests that they make a covenant of peace,

00:27:41.170 --> 00:27:46.170
ensuring that neither family will bring harm to the other.

00:27:46.170 --> 00:27:50.170
Laban's motive is not that he loves peace.

00:27:50.170 --> 00:27:54.170
It might have been to ensure that Jacob will not return

00:27:54.170 --> 00:27:57.170
with the household gods after Laban's death

00:27:57.170 --> 00:28:01.170
to deprive his sons of their inheritance.

00:28:01.170 --> 00:28:04.170
In any case, Jacob agrees.

00:28:04.170 --> 00:28:07.170
Everyone relaxes.

00:28:07.170 --> 00:28:09.170
There's to be no violence

00:28:09.170 --> 00:28:15.170
and a monument is set up to memorialize the agreement.

00:28:15.170 --> 00:28:19.170
Despite the many years of oppression,

00:28:19.170 --> 00:28:23.170
Jacob agrees to a covenant of peace.

00:28:23.170 --> 00:28:28.170
He does not harbor resentment or seek revenge.

00:28:28.170 --> 00:28:32.170
That crisis is over for Jacob.

00:28:32.170 --> 00:28:36.170
But now, another one looms.

00:28:36.170 --> 00:28:39.170
Jacob sends messengers to his brother.

00:28:39.170 --> 00:28:42.170
They say that Jacob is returning

00:28:42.170 --> 00:28:45.170
and that he seeks Esau's favor.

00:28:45.170 --> 00:28:48.170
The messengers return with the news

00:28:48.170 --> 00:28:51.170
that Esau is on his way to meet him

00:28:51.170 --> 00:28:54.170
and with him are 400 men.

00:28:54.170 --> 00:28:56.170
Oh my!

00:28:56.170 --> 00:28:59.170
Is Esau still angry?

00:28:59.170 --> 00:29:02.170
Understandably, Jacob is worried.

00:29:02.170 --> 00:29:06.170
He does not want to fight with his brother.

00:29:06.170 --> 00:29:09.170
Let us see how he handles the situation.

00:29:09.170 --> 00:29:14.170
Please turn to Genesis chapter 32 and verse 13.

00:29:14.170 --> 00:29:19.700
And he spent the night there.

00:29:19.700 --> 00:29:22.700
Then he took some of his possessions

00:29:22.700 --> 00:29:25.700
as a gift for Esau his brother.

00:29:25.700 --> 00:29:28.700
200 female goats.

00:29:28.700 --> 00:29:30.700
20 male goats.

00:29:30.700 --> 00:29:32.700
200 female sheep.

00:29:32.700 --> 00:29:34.700
20 rams.

00:29:34.700 --> 00:29:37.700
30 camels nursing their young.

00:29:37.700 --> 00:29:39.700
40 cows.

00:29:39.700 --> 00:29:41.700
10 bulls.

00:29:41.700 --> 00:29:43.700
20 female dokeys.

00:29:43.700 --> 00:29:47.700
And 10 full grown male dokeys.

00:29:47.700 --> 00:29:50.700
He handed them over to his servants.

00:29:50.700 --> 00:29:52.700
One drove after another.

00:29:52.700 --> 00:29:55.700
And he said to his servants.

00:29:55.700 --> 00:29:57.700
Cross over ahead of me.

00:29:57.700 --> 00:30:02.700
And you were to set a space between one drove and the next.

00:30:02.700 --> 00:30:05.700
He also commanded the first one.

00:30:05.700 --> 00:30:08.700
In case Esau my brother should meet you and ask,

00:30:08.700 --> 00:30:10.700
to whom do you belong?

00:30:10.700 --> 00:30:12.700
And where are you going?

00:30:12.700 --> 00:30:14.700
And to whom did these ahead of you belong?

00:30:14.700 --> 00:30:16.700
Then you should say,

00:30:16.700 --> 00:30:18.700
to your servant Jacob,

00:30:18.700 --> 00:30:21.700
it is a gift sent to my Lord,

00:30:21.700 --> 00:30:22.700
to Esau.

00:30:22.700 --> 00:30:26.700
And look, he himself is also behind us.

00:30:26.700 --> 00:30:29.700
And he commanded also the second,

00:30:29.700 --> 00:30:33.700
the third, and all those following the drools.

00:30:33.700 --> 00:30:35.700
According to this word,

00:30:35.700 --> 00:30:38.700
you are to speak to Esau when you meet him.

00:30:38.700 --> 00:30:40.700
And you should also say,

00:30:40.700 --> 00:30:44.700
here is your servant Jacob behind us.

00:30:44.700 --> 00:30:47.700
Before he said to himself,

00:30:47.700 --> 00:30:51.700
if I appease him by sending a gift ahead of me,

00:30:51.700 --> 00:30:54.700
then afterward when I see him,

00:30:54.700 --> 00:30:57.700
he may give me a kindly reception.

00:30:57.700 --> 00:31:03.390
Jacob wants peaceful relations with his brother.

00:31:03.390 --> 00:31:06.390
He sends a generous gift,

00:31:06.390 --> 00:31:08.390
hundreds of animals,

00:31:08.390 --> 00:31:10.390
to help make that possible.

00:31:10.390 --> 00:31:12.390
Was Jacob weak-minded,

00:31:12.390 --> 00:31:16.390
too cowardly to stand up to his brother?

00:31:16.390 --> 00:31:17.390
Not at all.

00:31:17.390 --> 00:31:20.390
Why, as the time neared for the meeting with Esau,

00:31:20.390 --> 00:31:24.390
Jacob wrestles with an angel until dawn,

00:31:24.390 --> 00:31:28.390
to receive further assurance of Jehovah's blessing.

00:31:28.390 --> 00:31:33.390
Let's now see what happens when the two brothers meet.

00:31:33.390 --> 00:31:40.440
Please turn to Genesis chapter 33 and verse 1.

00:31:40.440 --> 00:31:45.440
Now Jacob raised his eyes and saw Esau coming,

00:31:45.440 --> 00:31:49.440
and 400 men were with him.

00:31:49.440 --> 00:31:53.440
So he divided the children among Leah, Rachel,

00:31:53.440 --> 00:31:56.440
and the two female servants.

00:31:56.440 --> 00:32:00.440
He put the female servants and their children in front.

00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:03.440
Leah and her children after them,

00:32:03.440 --> 00:32:06.440
and Rachel and Joseph behind them,

00:32:06.440 --> 00:32:09.440
then he himself went ahead of them

00:32:09.440 --> 00:32:13.440
and bowed down to the earth seven times,

00:32:13.440 --> 00:32:16.440
as he came near to his brother.

00:32:16.440 --> 00:32:19.440
But Esau ran to meet him,

00:32:19.440 --> 00:32:22.440
and he embraced him and kissed him,

00:32:22.440 --> 00:32:25.440
and they burst into tears.

00:32:25.440 --> 00:32:30.440
When he raised his eyes and saw the women and the children,

00:32:30.440 --> 00:32:31.440
he said,

00:32:31.440 --> 00:32:33.440
Who are these with you?

00:32:33.440 --> 00:32:35.440
To which he said,

00:32:35.440 --> 00:32:39.440
The children with whom God has favored your servant.

00:32:39.440 --> 00:32:44.440
At that, the female servants came forward with their children,

00:32:44.440 --> 00:32:46.440
and bowed down.

00:32:46.440 --> 00:32:49.440
And Leah too came forward with her children,

00:32:49.440 --> 00:32:51.440
and they bowed down.

00:32:51.440 --> 00:32:54.440
Then Joseph came forward with Rachel,

00:32:54.440 --> 00:32:57.440
and they bowed down.

00:32:57.440 --> 00:32:59.440
Esau said,

00:32:59.440 --> 00:33:03.440
What is the purpose of all this camp of travelers that I have met?

00:33:03.440 --> 00:33:05.440
He replied,

00:33:05.440 --> 00:33:08.440
in order to find favor in the eyes of my Lord.

00:33:08.440 --> 00:33:10.440
Then Esau said,

00:33:10.440 --> 00:33:14.440
I have a great many possessions, my brother.

00:33:14.440 --> 00:33:17.440
Keep what is yours.

00:33:17.440 --> 00:33:19.440
However, Jacob said,

00:33:19.440 --> 00:33:22.440
No, please.

00:33:22.440 --> 00:33:25.440
If I have found favor in your eyes,

00:33:25.440 --> 00:33:28.440
you must take my gift from my hand,

00:33:28.440 --> 00:33:32.440
because I brought it so that I could see your face.

00:33:32.440 --> 00:33:36.440
And I have seen your face,

00:33:36.440 --> 00:33:38.440
as though seeing God's face,

00:33:38.440 --> 00:33:41.440
in that you received me with pleasure.

00:33:41.440 --> 00:33:44.440
Take, please,

00:33:44.440 --> 00:33:48.440
the gift conveying my blessing that was brought to you.

00:33:48.440 --> 00:33:51.440
For God has favored me,

00:33:51.440 --> 00:33:54.440
and I have everything I need.

00:33:54.440 --> 00:33:57.440
And he continued to urge him,

00:33:57.440 --> 00:34:02.329
so that he took it.

00:34:02.329 --> 00:34:04.329
What a happy outcome.

00:34:04.329 --> 00:34:07.329
Instead of an angry confrontation,

00:34:07.329 --> 00:34:10.329
there is a joyful reunion.

00:34:10.329 --> 00:34:12.329
The two men shed tears.

00:34:12.329 --> 00:34:15.329
They embrace again.

00:34:15.329 --> 00:34:18.329
Jacob is the peacemaker.

00:34:18.329 --> 00:34:20.329
How did he prove that?

00:34:20.329 --> 00:34:22.329
He prayed,

00:34:22.329 --> 00:34:25.329
and he acted in harmony with his prayers.

00:34:25.329 --> 00:34:27.329
He sent gifts.

00:34:27.329 --> 00:34:30.329
He showed honor and respect to his brother,

00:34:30.329 --> 00:34:32.329
calling him Lord,

00:34:32.329 --> 00:34:35.329
and bowing seven times.

00:34:35.329 --> 00:34:37.329
What's the lesson?

00:34:37.329 --> 00:34:43.329
Doesn't this account well illustrate the extent to which we should be willing to go

00:34:43.329 --> 00:34:47.329
to preserve peace with our Christian brothers and sisters?

00:34:47.329 --> 00:34:53.800
We learn so much about seeking peace from Jacob.

00:34:53.800 --> 00:34:56.800
When threatened by his brother while living at home,

00:34:56.800 --> 00:34:58.800
he moved away.

00:34:58.800 --> 00:35:02.800
When deceived by Laban regarding Rachel and Leah,

00:35:02.800 --> 00:35:04.800
he yielded.

00:35:04.800 --> 00:35:07.800
When chased down and accused by Laban,

00:35:07.800 --> 00:35:11.800
Jacob agreed to a covenant of peace.

00:35:11.800 --> 00:35:14.800
And when confronting Esau,

00:35:14.800 --> 00:35:16.800
he offered a gift.

00:35:16.800 --> 00:35:18.800
Keep in mind,

00:35:18.800 --> 00:35:23.800
in none of these situations was Jacob the one who needed to apologize,

00:35:23.800 --> 00:35:26.800
yet throughout his life,

00:35:26.800 --> 00:35:29.800
Jacob loved peace.

00:35:29.800 --> 00:35:32.800
He relied on Jehovah

00:35:32.800 --> 00:35:35.800
and Jehovah blessed him.

00:35:35.800 --> 00:35:37.800
Jehovah never forgot Jacob

00:35:37.800 --> 00:35:40.800
and how he pursued peace

00:35:40.800 --> 00:35:43.800
in his dealings with others.

00:35:43.800 --> 00:35:45.800
When we do the same,

00:35:45.800 --> 00:35:50.800
when we pursue peace in the face of injustice,

00:35:50.800 --> 00:35:52.800
in the face of persecution,

00:35:52.800 --> 00:35:54.800
in small issues,

00:35:54.800 --> 00:35:56.800
as well as in big issues.

00:35:56.800 --> 00:35:59.800
Jehovah will not forget us either.

00:35:59.800 --> 00:36:02.800
Jehovah will richly bless us

00:36:02.800 --> 00:36:04.800
if we love peace

00:36:04.800 --> 00:36:08.800
just as Jacob loved peace.

00:36:08.800 --> 00:36:17.489
How comforting it is

00:36:17.489 --> 00:36:20.489
to reflect on Jehovah's love

00:36:20.489 --> 00:36:23.489
and support for those who make peace.

00:36:23.489 --> 00:36:28.489
This Bible account is filled with practical examples

00:36:28.489 --> 00:36:31.489
that each of us can imitate.

