00:37:01.750 --> 00:37:03.750
a helper to the teaching committee.

00:37:03.750 --> 00:37:06.750
As he answers this question in the talk,

00:37:06.750 --> 00:37:19.460
the result of true righteousness will be peace.

00:37:19.460 --> 00:37:21.460
Earlier, we considered the expression

00:37:21.460 --> 00:37:23.460
at Philippians 4.7,

00:37:23.460 --> 00:37:27.460
the peace of God that surpasses all understanding.

00:37:27.460 --> 00:37:29.460
That is, the tranquility

00:37:29.460 --> 00:37:31.460
and calmness we enjoy

00:37:31.460 --> 00:37:34.460
because we have a close friendship with Jehovah.

00:37:34.460 --> 00:37:37.460
What a remarkable blessing.

00:37:37.460 --> 00:37:40.460
But although we enjoy God-given peace,

00:37:40.460 --> 00:37:42.460
our life in this system of things

00:37:42.460 --> 00:37:45.460
is not problem-free, is it?

00:37:45.460 --> 00:37:47.460
Psalm 34 19 acknowledges as much

00:37:47.460 --> 00:37:48.460
when it says,

00:37:48.460 --> 00:37:52.460
many are the hardships of the righteous one.

00:37:52.460 --> 00:37:57.460
But Jehovah rescues him from them all.

00:37:57.460 --> 00:38:00.460
We may experience family opposition,

00:38:00.460 --> 00:38:03.460
persecution, war, natural disasters,

00:38:03.460 --> 00:38:05.460
or severe illnesses.

00:38:05.460 --> 00:38:07.460
But none of these hardships

00:38:07.460 --> 00:38:10.460
can separate us from God's love.

00:38:10.460 --> 00:38:11.460
Neither death nor life,

00:38:11.460 --> 00:38:12.460
nor angels, nor governments,

00:38:12.460 --> 00:38:13.460
nor things now here,

00:38:13.460 --> 00:38:14.460
nor things to come.

00:38:14.460 --> 00:38:16.460
None of these things can rob us

00:38:16.460 --> 00:38:20.460
of the peace Jehovah gives.

00:38:20.460 --> 00:38:25.460
And yet there is something that can.

00:38:25.460 --> 00:38:31.460
Please turn with me to Isaiah chapter 32, verse 17.

00:38:31.460 --> 00:38:33.460
And as we read this text,

00:38:33.460 --> 00:38:37.460
notice that it refers to peace as a result.

00:38:37.460 --> 00:38:40.460
Do you think of peace that way as a result?

00:38:40.460 --> 00:38:43.460
If peace is a result,

00:38:43.460 --> 00:38:45.460
what causes it?

00:38:45.460 --> 00:38:49.460
Isaiah 32, 17.

00:38:49.460 --> 00:38:54.460
The result of true righteousness

00:38:54.460 --> 00:38:56.460
will be peace.

00:38:56.460 --> 00:39:00.460
And the fruitage of true righteousness

00:39:00.460 --> 00:39:05.460
will be lasting tranquility and security.

00:39:05.460 --> 00:39:07.460
What a beautiful expression,

00:39:07.460 --> 00:39:11.460
lasting tranquility and security.

00:39:11.460 --> 00:39:15.460
Again, from what does it result?

00:39:15.460 --> 00:39:17.460
True righteousness.

00:39:17.460 --> 00:39:19.460
What if righteousness no longer mattered to us?

00:39:19.460 --> 00:39:22.460
What if a person concluded it makes no difference how I live

00:39:22.460 --> 00:39:24.460
or what sacrifices I make?

00:39:24.460 --> 00:39:26.460
If I'm going to suffer hardships either way,

00:39:26.460 --> 00:39:29.460
I might as well do whatever I please while I can.

00:39:29.460 --> 00:39:32.460
What's wrong with that thinking?

00:39:32.460 --> 00:39:36.460
Would it show appreciation for peace

00:39:36.460 --> 00:39:39.460
and all that Jehovah has done to make it possible?

00:39:39.460 --> 00:39:41.460
Peace is a result.

00:39:41.460 --> 00:39:44.460
And behind every result is a cause.

00:39:44.460 --> 00:39:46.460
If we want peace,

00:39:46.460 --> 00:39:49.460
we have to pursue righteousness.

00:39:49.460 --> 00:39:53.460
An unrighteous person cannot be at peace with God.

00:39:53.460 --> 00:39:58.460
Serious transgressions put a strain on a person's relationship with God.

00:39:58.460 --> 00:40:03.460
King David's words found at Psalm 38-3,

00:40:03.460 --> 00:40:07.460
sensing Jehovah's disapproval, he wrote,

00:40:07.460 --> 00:40:11.460
there is no peace within my bones

00:40:11.460 --> 00:40:14.460
because of my sin.

00:40:14.460 --> 00:40:18.460
Inevitably, the unrighteous person will reap what he sows

00:40:18.460 --> 00:40:22.460
and lose his peace.

00:40:22.460 --> 00:40:24.460
What is righteousness?

00:40:24.460 --> 00:40:27.460
And how do we pursue it?

00:40:27.460 --> 00:40:30.460
Righteousness is what we have or what we show

00:40:30.460 --> 00:40:33.460
when we do what is right according to Jehovah's standards.

00:40:33.460 --> 00:40:36.460
And those standards are not just rules we follow

00:40:36.460 --> 00:40:40.460
but principles that guide the way we deal with each other.

00:40:40.460 --> 00:40:43.460
As universal sovereign and creator,

00:40:43.460 --> 00:40:46.460
Jehovah God determines what is righteous.

00:40:46.460 --> 00:40:48.460
Isn't that what was represented by the tree

00:40:48.460 --> 00:40:51.460
of the knowledge of good and bad in the Garden of Eden?

00:40:51.460 --> 00:40:54.460
As a result of Jehovah's command to abstain from its fruit,

00:40:54.460 --> 00:40:57.460
that tree represented God's right

00:40:57.460 --> 00:40:59.460
to determine for his creatures what is good

00:40:59.460 --> 00:41:02.460
and what is bad for them.

00:41:02.460 --> 00:41:05.460
And although Jehovah has given humans free will,

00:41:05.460 --> 00:41:07.460
the right to choose,

00:41:07.460 --> 00:41:10.460
he has not granted humans, not even perfect ones,

00:41:10.460 --> 00:41:13.460
the right to set the standard for what is righteous

00:41:13.460 --> 00:41:15.460
and what is not.

00:41:15.460 --> 00:41:19.460
Now notice once again that Isaiah 32-17 says

00:41:19.460 --> 00:41:24.460
that the result of true righteousness will be peace.

00:41:24.460 --> 00:41:28.460
It uses that term twice, true righteousness.

00:41:28.460 --> 00:41:33.460
Not everything called righteousness is true righteousness.

00:41:33.460 --> 00:41:36.460
Many people view righteousness as just a personal virtue

00:41:36.460 --> 00:41:39.460
achieved by following the rules.

00:41:39.460 --> 00:41:43.460
At Matthew 23-28, Jesus said that the Pharisees

00:41:43.460 --> 00:41:45.460
appeared righteous on the outside,

00:41:45.460 --> 00:41:48.460
but inside they were lawless.

00:41:49.460 --> 00:41:54.460
Ecclesiastes 7-16 talks about those who think their standards

00:41:54.460 --> 00:41:57.460
are more righteous even than gods.

00:41:57.460 --> 00:42:00.460
And at Romans 10-3, Paul talked about people

00:42:00.460 --> 00:42:05.460
who seek to establish their own righteousness.

00:42:05.460 --> 00:42:08.460
But false piety over righteousness

00:42:08.460 --> 00:42:15.460
and self-righteousness are not what Isaiah 32-17 is talking about.

00:42:15.460 --> 00:42:19.460
Today many argue for the acceptance of conduct

00:42:19.460 --> 00:42:21.460
that Jehovah forbids.

00:42:21.460 --> 00:42:24.460
They may even find support from a world

00:42:24.460 --> 00:42:27.460
already alienated from God.

00:42:27.460 --> 00:42:30.460
But wide acceptance in a growing community

00:42:30.460 --> 00:42:33.460
does not redefine righteousness.

00:42:33.460 --> 00:42:36.460
None of that is true righteousness.

00:42:36.460 --> 00:42:39.460
Our loving creator sets the standard for what is right.

00:42:39.460 --> 00:42:43.460
Not our feelings, not the community at large.

00:42:44.460 --> 00:42:46.460
Now while you're here in Isaiah,

00:42:46.460 --> 00:42:49.460
please turn to chapter 48.

00:42:49.460 --> 00:42:53.460
In order to be viewed as righteous,

00:42:53.460 --> 00:42:56.460
we have to trust that Jehovah

00:42:56.460 --> 00:42:58.460
should set the standard of right and wrong.

00:42:58.460 --> 00:43:01.460
In addition, we must prove by our speech and actions

00:43:01.460 --> 00:43:05.460
that we agree with Jehovah's standards and obey him.

00:43:05.460 --> 00:43:10.460
And that takes real courage in a wicked world.

00:43:10.460 --> 00:43:13.460
But when we do that, we enjoy the result.

00:43:13.460 --> 00:43:15.460
Notice what it says at Isaiah,

00:43:15.460 --> 00:43:20.460
chapter 48 verses 17 and 18.

00:43:20.460 --> 00:43:22.460
This is what Jehovah says.

00:43:22.460 --> 00:43:25.460
You are repurchaser.

00:43:25.460 --> 00:43:28.460
The holy one of Israel.

00:43:28.460 --> 00:43:31.460
I Jehovah am your God.

00:43:31.460 --> 00:43:34.460
The one teaching you to benefit yourself

00:43:34.460 --> 00:43:35.460
or as the footnote says,

00:43:35.460 --> 00:43:38.460
teaching you for your own good.

00:43:38.460 --> 00:43:42.460
The one guiding you in the way you should walk.

00:43:42.460 --> 00:43:46.460
If only you would pay attention to my commandments,

00:43:46.460 --> 00:43:51.460
then your peace would become just like a river

00:43:51.460 --> 00:43:56.460
and your righteousness like the waves of the sea.

00:43:56.460 --> 00:43:59.460
Paying attention to Jehovah's commandments

00:43:59.460 --> 00:44:01.460
results in two things.

00:44:01.460 --> 00:44:06.460
First, our peace will become just like a river,

00:44:06.460 --> 00:44:10.460
serene, abundant, ongoing.

00:44:10.460 --> 00:44:15.460
Second, our righteousness will be like the waves of the sea.

00:44:15.460 --> 00:44:18.460
Remember your last trip to the beach?

00:44:18.460 --> 00:44:20.460
As you stood there on the shore,

00:44:20.460 --> 00:44:22.460
perhaps on a high hill overlooking the ocean,

00:44:22.460 --> 00:44:25.460
watching the waves roll in one after the other,

00:44:25.460 --> 00:44:28.460
just as they have for thousands of years,

00:44:28.460 --> 00:44:32.460
could you feel a sense of constancy?

00:44:32.460 --> 00:44:35.460
Jehovah says that our course of doing what is right

00:44:35.460 --> 00:44:37.460
can be just like that.

00:44:37.460 --> 00:44:40.460
He will guide us in the path of righteousness.

00:44:40.460 --> 00:44:43.460
He will bless us with unending peace.

00:44:43.460 --> 00:44:48.460
In the process, we learn through experience.

00:44:48.460 --> 00:44:53.460
How Jehovah's wise and loving ways truly benefit us personally.

00:44:53.460 --> 00:44:55.460
But if we refuse to do that,

00:44:55.460 --> 00:44:58.460
we learn what agitation and discord truly mean.

00:44:58.460 --> 00:45:00.460
As verse 22 says,

00:45:00.460 --> 00:45:06.460
there is no peace, says Jehovah, for the wicked.

00:45:06.460 --> 00:45:09.460
It's not a heavy-handed threat to manipulate human behavior

00:45:09.460 --> 00:45:11.460
as if Jehovah needed to do that.

00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:15.460
It's a fact, a truth, a timeless principle.

00:45:15.460 --> 00:45:17.460
God is love.

00:45:17.460 --> 00:45:21.460
He teaches us for our own good and the result,

00:45:21.460 --> 00:45:25.460
if we pay attention, is peace.

00:45:25.460 --> 00:45:29.460
Isaiah 48, 17, and 18.

00:45:29.460 --> 00:45:38.460
And these verses assure us that imperfect humans truly can have a righteous standing with God.

00:45:38.460 --> 00:45:40.460
Let's explore that further.

00:45:40.460 --> 00:45:47.460
Do you recall the very first time the word righteous is used in the Bible?

00:45:47.460 --> 00:45:50.460
Turn with me, please, to Genesis chapter 6.

00:45:50.460 --> 00:45:53.460
Now you likely recognize this is the account about Noah.

00:45:53.460 --> 00:45:56.460
Noah lived in an extremely wicked world.

00:45:57.460 --> 00:46:00.460
During his lifetime, rebel angels left their assignments in heaven,

00:46:00.460 --> 00:46:03.460
materialized, married human women,

00:46:03.460 --> 00:46:07.460
and fathered hybrid offspring who became violent giants.

00:46:07.460 --> 00:46:12.460
Now how did all of that wickedness and violence affect Jehovah?

00:46:12.460 --> 00:46:15.460
According to Genesis 6.6,

00:46:15.460 --> 00:46:18.460
his heart was saddened,

00:46:18.460 --> 00:46:21.460
which is a remarkable thing to contemplate, isn't it?

00:46:21.460 --> 00:46:24.460
Jehovah's feelings are affected by our decisions

00:46:24.460 --> 00:46:27.460
because he cares for us.

00:46:27.460 --> 00:46:34.460
That ancient world became so wicked that Jehovah decided it must be destroyed.

00:46:34.460 --> 00:46:37.460
And yet right in the midst of all this depravity,

00:46:37.460 --> 00:46:40.460
Noah showed a different spirit.

00:46:40.460 --> 00:46:46.460
Notice what it says at Genesis chapter 6 verses 8 and 9.

00:46:46.460 --> 00:46:51.460
But Noah found favor in the eyes of Jehovah.

00:46:52.460 --> 00:46:55.460
This is the history of Noah.

00:46:55.460 --> 00:46:59.460
Noah was a righteous man.

00:46:59.460 --> 00:47:00.460
There it is.

00:47:00.460 --> 00:47:04.460
And why was he described as righteous?

00:47:04.460 --> 00:47:10.460
He proved himself faultless among his contemporaries.

00:47:10.460 --> 00:47:14.460
Yes, Noah was not like the rebel angels or their offspring,

00:47:14.460 --> 00:47:16.460
or like degraded human society.

00:47:16.460 --> 00:47:20.460
Noah walked with the true God.

00:47:21.460 --> 00:47:25.460
And thus the second time we find the word righteous

00:47:25.460 --> 00:47:29.460
is at Genesis chapter 7 and verse 1.

00:47:29.460 --> 00:47:32.460
After that, Jehovah said to Noah,

00:47:32.460 --> 00:47:33.460
go into the art.

00:47:33.460 --> 00:47:39.460
You and all your household because you are the one I have found

00:47:39.460 --> 00:47:45.460
to be righteous before me among this generation.

00:47:45.460 --> 00:47:47.460
Because of Noah's righteousness,

00:47:47.460 --> 00:47:50.460
he and his family survived the flood.

00:47:51.460 --> 00:47:54.460
To worship Jehovah on a cleansed earth.

00:47:54.460 --> 00:47:57.460
And after the waters subsided,

00:47:57.460 --> 00:48:00.460
and the family emerged from the ark,

00:48:00.460 --> 00:48:03.460
they witnessed a splendid sight.

00:48:03.460 --> 00:48:10.460
One never before observed a serene multi-colored arch in the sky,

00:48:10.460 --> 00:48:16.460
a rainbow, a reassuring indication of peace with God,

00:48:16.460 --> 00:48:20.460
peace, resulting from righteousness.

00:48:20.460 --> 00:48:25.460
And where does the word righteous appear next in the Bible?

00:48:25.460 --> 00:48:27.460
In the account about Abraham,

00:48:27.460 --> 00:48:30.460
notably in his famous conversation with Jehovah,

00:48:30.460 --> 00:48:33.460
found at Genesis chapter 18,

00:48:33.460 --> 00:48:35.460
where Jehovah promised Abraham that if he found as few

00:48:35.460 --> 00:48:38.460
as ten righteous people in the city of Sodom,

00:48:38.460 --> 00:48:41.460
he would not destroy that city.

00:48:41.460 --> 00:48:45.460
Now, what was it that distinguished Abraham as righteous

00:48:45.460 --> 00:48:48.460
in that moral climate?

00:48:48.460 --> 00:48:51.460
As you read Genesis chapters 12 through 22,

00:48:51.460 --> 00:48:55.460
you get the sense that Abraham was a man of great faith,

00:48:55.460 --> 00:48:56.460
unwavering faith.

00:48:56.460 --> 00:48:59.460
He was ready to do whatever Jehovah asked of him.

00:48:59.460 --> 00:49:04.460
Now, citing Genesis chapter 15 and verse 6 and other texts,

00:49:04.460 --> 00:49:11.460
James 223 says that Abraham put faith in Jehovah.

00:49:11.460 --> 00:49:16.460
And it was counted to him as righteousness.

00:49:16.460 --> 00:49:21.460
And he came to be called Jehovah's Friend.

00:49:21.460 --> 00:49:24.460
Jehovah's Friend.

00:49:24.460 --> 00:49:30.460
Peace with God, resulting from righteousness.

00:49:30.460 --> 00:49:33.460
Now, what about God's people today?

00:49:33.460 --> 00:49:37.460
Turn with me, please, to Isaiah chapter 60.

00:49:37.460 --> 00:49:41.460
Isaiah chapter 60.

00:49:41.460 --> 00:49:47.460
Jehovah refers to Noah and Abraham as righteous.

00:49:47.460 --> 00:49:50.460
But what would he say about you and me?

00:49:50.460 --> 00:49:53.460
Well, notice what it says toward the end of this chapter.

00:49:53.460 --> 00:50:00.460
Isaiah 60 verses 21 and 22.

00:50:00.460 --> 00:50:08.059
And all your people will be righteous.

00:50:08.059 --> 00:50:12.059
They will possess the land forever.

00:50:12.059 --> 00:50:15.059
They are the sprout that I planted,

00:50:15.059 --> 00:50:18.059
the work of my hands for me to be beautified,

00:50:18.059 --> 00:50:20.059
the little one will become a thousand,

00:50:20.059 --> 00:50:22.059
and the small one a mighty nation,

00:50:22.059 --> 00:50:28.059
I myself, Jehovah, will speed it up in its own time.

00:50:28.059 --> 00:50:31.059
Yes, prospective members of the great crowd

00:50:31.059 --> 00:50:35.059
have been declared righteous as friends of God,

00:50:35.059 --> 00:50:37.059
as Abraham was.

00:50:37.059 --> 00:50:42.059
In Jehovah's eyes, they are, as it says in Revelation chapter 7 and verse 9,

00:50:42.059 --> 00:50:44.059
dressed in white robes.

00:50:44.059 --> 00:50:48.059
Today, they're serving alongside God's spirit- anointed ones

00:50:48.059 --> 00:50:51.059
who were declared righteous for life.

00:50:51.059 --> 00:50:54.059
Jehovah, our repurchaser,

00:50:54.059 --> 00:50:59.059
the holy one of Israel has bought us back from bondage to sin

00:50:59.059 --> 00:51:04.059
and death through the ransom sacrifice of Jesus Christ,

00:51:04.059 --> 00:51:09.059
and thus with faith in the ransom sacrifice of Jesus Christ,

00:51:09.059 --> 00:51:14.059
imperfect people are considered righteous in the sight of God.

00:51:14.059 --> 00:51:18.059
Now, in calling us righteous, Jehovah God by means of Jesus,

00:51:18.059 --> 00:51:21.059
has done something for us that we could not do for ourselves

00:51:21.059 --> 00:51:23.059
in our imperfect condition.

00:51:23.059 --> 00:51:27.059
But does that mean that we can do no wrong?

00:51:27.059 --> 00:51:31.059
No, it does not mean that.

00:51:31.059 --> 00:51:38.059
In order to maintain our peace, we must cooperate with Jehovah.

00:51:38.059 --> 00:51:42.059
Turn with me, please, to Romans chapter 1.

00:51:42.059 --> 00:51:46.059
Now, at light, Noah and Abraham,

00:51:46.059 --> 00:51:49.059
we live in a wicked and violent world where we are exposed

00:51:49.059 --> 00:51:54.059
to a spirit of disobedience, Satan wants us to become part of this world

00:51:54.059 --> 00:51:58.059
by adopting its unrighteous standards.

00:51:59.059 --> 00:52:02.059
In the world, sexual immorality is practiced without shame.

00:52:02.059 --> 00:52:05.059
Homosexuals flaunt their conduct,

00:52:05.059 --> 00:52:11.059
but Jehovah tells us that homosexual acts are unrighteous.

00:52:11.059 --> 00:52:16.059
God specifically warned the Israelites against this

00:52:16.059 --> 00:52:18.059
and other forms of immorality.

00:52:18.059 --> 00:52:27.059
Leviticus chapter 18 and verse 22 says that homosexual acts are detestable.

00:52:27.059 --> 00:52:30.059
Jehovah still find it so offensive?

00:52:30.059 --> 00:52:34.059
Well, notice what he inspired for both Jews and non-Jews

00:52:34.059 --> 00:52:41.059
in the Christian Greek scriptures here at Romans chapter 1 verses 26 and 27.

00:52:41.059 --> 00:52:48.059
That is why God gave them over to disgraceful sexual passion.

00:52:48.059 --> 00:52:52.059
For their females changed the natural use of themselves

00:52:52.059 --> 00:52:54.059
into one contrary to nature.

00:52:54.059 --> 00:52:58.059
Likewise, also the males left the natural use of the female

00:52:58.059 --> 00:53:02.059
and became violently inflamed in their lust toward one another.

00:53:02.059 --> 00:53:05.059
Males with males working with his obscene

00:53:05.059 --> 00:53:11.059
and receiving in themselves the full penalty which was due for their error.

00:53:11.059 --> 00:53:15.059
So, Jehovah has not changed.

00:53:15.059 --> 00:53:23.059
According to the creator, homosexual acts constitute disgraceful obscene error.

00:53:24.059 --> 00:53:26.059
Some would disagree.

00:53:26.059 --> 00:53:28.059
As verse 28 points out,

00:53:28.059 --> 00:53:33.059
such ones do not consider it worthwhile to acknowledge God,

00:53:33.059 --> 00:53:35.059
but with what result?

00:53:35.059 --> 00:53:37.059
As it says there,

00:53:37.059 --> 00:53:42.059
a disapproved mental state, just the opposite of peace.

00:53:42.059 --> 00:53:46.059
And merely approving of unrighteous conduct,

00:53:46.059 --> 00:53:47.059
displeases Jehovah.

00:53:47.059 --> 00:53:51.059
Notice how this is indicated in verse 32.

00:53:51.059 --> 00:53:55.059
Although these know full well the righteous decree of God

00:53:55.059 --> 00:53:59.059
that those practicing such things are deserving of death,

00:53:59.059 --> 00:54:01.059
they not only keep on doing them,

00:54:01.059 --> 00:54:06.059
but also approve of those practicing them.

00:54:06.059 --> 00:54:12.059
Still, we do not hate individuals who practice unrighteousness

00:54:12.059 --> 00:54:13.059
